1
00:00:02,208 --> 00:00:05,166
[ Playing "Love's Sorrow" ]

2
00:00:05,250 --> 00:00:11,666
♪♪

3
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:13,458
[ Sighs ]

4
00:00:13,541 --> 00:00:15,416
[ Door opens ]
[ Playing stops ]

5
00:00:17,791 --> 00:00:19,375
[ Sighs ] Please.

6
00:00:19,458 --> 00:00:21,833
You know darn well
I'm gonna say yes.

7
00:00:21,916 --> 00:00:24,166
[ Sighs ]

8
00:00:28,458 --> 00:00:29,791
♪ Hubby is a dummy ♪

9
00:00:31,583 --> 00:00:33,250
♪ So watch your ass,
honey ♪

10
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:35,125
♪ Or I'mma kick you out ♪

11
00:00:36,041 --> 00:00:38,500
[ Humming melody ]
Hiroko,

12
00:00:38,583 --> 00:00:39,833
did you and your husband
get in another fight?

13
00:00:39,916 --> 00:00:43,166
[ Scoffs ]
This is no mere fight.

14
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:44,666
It's way more epic
than that.

15
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:47,375
If he doesn't say sorry,
we're splitsville.

16
00:00:47,458 --> 00:00:48,791
Oh.

17
00:00:53,375 --> 00:00:55,375
♪ Hubby is a dummy ♪

18
00:00:57,291 --> 00:00:58,875
♪ Watch your ass,
honey ♪

19
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:00,208
♪ Or I'mma kick you out ♪

20
00:01:00,291 --> 00:01:01,708
What the -- Kousei.

21
00:01:01,791 --> 00:01:04,583
How are you
doing that?

22
00:01:05,583 --> 00:01:06,208
Hmm?

23
00:01:06,291 --> 00:01:09,208
I just play,
same as you.

24
00:01:09,291 --> 00:01:10,708
[ Gasps ]

25
00:01:10,791 --> 00:01:12,250
Hiroko:<i> Saki!</i>

26
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:14,208
<i>Now you've got to</i>
<i>make him a pianist!</i>

27
00:01:15,416 --> 00:01:16,708
<i>Listen to me.</i>

28
00:01:16,791 --> 00:01:20,708
<i>Your little boy is a genius!</i>

29
00:01:20,791 --> 00:01:22,750
[ "Nanairo Symphony" playing ]

30
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:25,791
♪♪

31
00:01:25,875 --> 00:01:29,583
[ Singing in Japanese ]

32
00:01:29,666 --> 00:01:38,708
♪♪

33
00:01:38,791 --> 00:01:47,750
♪♪

34
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:56,875
♪♪

35
00:01:56,958 --> 00:02:05,916
♪♪

36
00:02:06,041 --> 00:02:15,083
♪♪

37
00:02:15,166 --> 00:02:24,125
♪♪

38
00:02:24,208 --> 00:02:33,250
♪♪

39
00:02:33,333 --> 00:02:42,291
♪♪

40
00:02:42,375 --> 00:02:51,333
♪♪

41
00:02:51,416 --> 00:02:53,291
[ Audience murmuring ]

42
00:02:55,916 --> 00:02:58,333
Kousei:
Well, it's time.

43
00:02:58,416 --> 00:02:59,125
Wait.
By yourself?

44
00:02:59,208 --> 00:03:00,666
Yeah.
You're serious?

45
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:03,250
I am.
[ Sighs ]

46
00:03:03,333 --> 00:03:04,833
Well, what are you
going to play?

47
00:03:04,916 --> 00:03:06,000
Without the violin,
it doesn't --

48
00:03:06,083 --> 00:03:08,166
I'm keeping our song.
Huh?

49
00:03:08,250 --> 00:03:11,208
When she plays, it's nothing
more than a bunch of noise.

50
00:03:11,291 --> 00:03:12,750
Miike threw down
the gauntlet,

51
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:16,083
so I am picking it up.

52
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:18,708
I'll prove she's great,

53
00:03:18,791 --> 00:03:20,083
with or without her.

54
00:03:20,166 --> 00:03:21,333
[ Sighs ]

55
00:03:21,416 --> 00:03:22,833
Besides...

56
00:03:22,916 --> 00:03:25,333
I think Her Highness
will get a kick out of this.

57
00:03:25,416 --> 00:03:29,166
I mean, she did want our song
to stand out today.

58
00:03:29,250 --> 00:03:30,416
[ Applause ]

59
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:33,250
Today's a violin concert, right,
so what's the deal?

60
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:35,458
Does he mean
to play it on his own?

61
00:03:35,541 --> 00:03:38,333
<i>This is all</i>
<i>your fault, you know?</i>

62
00:03:38,416 --> 00:03:41,208
<i>You're the one</i>
<i>who pushed me back onstage.</i>

63
00:03:41,291 --> 00:03:44,583
<i>Even now,</i>
<i>I feel you under my skin.</i>

64
00:03:46,791 --> 00:03:48,375
<i>I want this.</i>

65
00:03:48,458 --> 00:03:49,083
<i>More than ever.</i>

66
00:03:49,166 --> 00:03:51,375
<i>More than anything.</i>

67
00:03:51,458 --> 00:03:53,708
<i>And so do I!</i>

68
00:03:53,791 --> 00:03:55,458
Hmm.
[ Gasps ]

69
00:03:55,541 --> 00:03:57,666
<i>Time to prove it,</i>

70
00:03:57,750 --> 00:03:59,375
<i>that I'm incredible.</i>

71
00:03:59,458 --> 00:04:01,291
<i>And if she chose me</i>
<i>to accompany her,</i>

72
00:04:01,375 --> 00:04:03,875
<i>that means she's even better.</i>

73
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:06,583
[ Playing "Love's Sorrow" ]

74
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:14,333
<i>Thumbing his nose</i>
<i>at convention yet again!</i>

75
00:04:14,416 --> 00:04:15,375
<i>Damn that Arima!</i>

76
00:04:15,458 --> 00:04:19,166
<i>This is more</i>
<i>than just half a duet.</i>

77
00:04:19,250 --> 00:04:21,416
<i>"Love's Sorrow,"</i>

78
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:23,875
<i>Rachmaninoff's</i>
<i>piano arrangement,</i>

79
00:04:23,958 --> 00:04:26,250
<i>and he's playing it</i>
<i>from memory.</i>

80
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:28,583
[ "Love's Sorrow" continues ]

81
00:04:28,666 --> 00:04:32,125
♪♪

82
00:04:32,208 --> 00:04:34,625
<i>Saki adored that song.</i>

83
00:04:34,708 --> 00:04:40,166
<i>All these years,</i>
<i>it's echoed in you, but...</i>

84
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:43,875
<i>your mom never</i>
<i>infused the notes</i>

85
00:04:43,958 --> 00:04:45,750
<i>with so much frustration.</i>

86
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:51,583
♪♪

87
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:56,666
♪♪

88
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:58,958
Kousei:<i> Watch me.</i>

89
00:04:59,041 --> 00:05:01,208
<i>Don't you dare look away.</i>

90
00:05:01,291 --> 00:05:03,166
<i>See how good I am?</i>

91
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:07,458
<i>Well, my partner</i>
<i>is even better!</i>

92
00:05:09,875 --> 00:05:11,625
<i>Look at him go.</i>

93
00:05:11,708 --> 00:05:13,041
<i>He's so passionate.</i>

94
00:05:13,125 --> 00:05:14,458
[ Sighs ]

95
00:05:15,125 --> 00:05:17,375
<i>What a letdown.</i>

96
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:20,125
<i>He's throwing a tantrum</i>
<i>at the keys.</i>

97
00:05:20,208 --> 00:05:23,791
<i>This brute force is a far cry</i>
<i>from true ferocity.</i>

98
00:05:23,875 --> 00:05:25,875
<i>It's so grating.</i>

99
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:27,625
[ Distorted music playing ]

100
00:05:27,708 --> 00:05:30,166
[ Keys pounding ]
<i>Hold on. The keys,</i>

101
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:32,000
<i>how hard am I pounding them</i>
<i>right now?</i>

102
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:35,875
<i>My spine is taut as piano wire.</i>

103
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:38,000
<i>This is a mess.</i>

104
00:05:38,083 --> 00:05:38,833
[ Bubbles popping ]

105
00:05:38,916 --> 00:05:40,375
<i>It's not right.</i>

106
00:05:40,458 --> 00:05:43,833
<i>This isn't how it's</i>
<i>supposed to sound.</i>

107
00:05:45,208 --> 00:05:48,166
<i>I heard her play it</i>
<i>a thousand times.</i>

108
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:50,833
<i>She'd lull me off</i>
<i>to sleep with it.</i>

109
00:05:50,916 --> 00:05:52,791
<i>I don't get it.</i>

110
00:05:52,875 --> 00:05:55,875
[ Tones thumping ]

111
00:05:58,541 --> 00:06:00,166
<i>Nothing has changed.</i>

112
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:03,500
<i>I can't hear my piano</i>
<i>for the life of me...</i>

113
00:06:03,583 --> 00:06:04,583
[ Tones thumping ]

114
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:07,166
<i>but I can hear what's inside.</i>

115
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:09,375
<i>All it means is that</i>
<i>you're not limited</i>

116
00:06:09,458 --> 00:06:11,583
<i>to whatever your ears</i>
<i>are picking up.</i>

117
00:06:11,666 --> 00:06:13,166
<i>Haven't you ever felt them</i>

118
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:16,041
<i>soaking into</i>
<i>those muted notes you play?</i>

119
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:16,333
[ Gasps ]

120
00:06:18,458 --> 00:06:20,375
<i>Don't think of it</i>
<i>as a handicap.</i>

121
00:06:20,458 --> 00:06:24,541
<i>Losing your notes,</i>
<i>it might be a gift.</i>

122
00:06:25,791 --> 00:06:27,083
Saki:<i> Kousei.</i>

123
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:29,166
<i>Play it more gently.</i>

124
00:06:29,250 --> 00:06:31,291
<i>Touch it like you're</i>
<i>holding a little baby.</i>

125
00:06:35,625 --> 00:06:38,750
<i>Just like</i>
<i>how I used to hold you.</i>

126
00:06:40,208 --> 00:06:41,791
[ Sighs ]

127
00:06:42,791 --> 00:06:44,708
<i>Mom.</i>

128
00:06:45,416 --> 00:06:47,750
<i>If you were here,</i>

129
00:06:47,833 --> 00:06:49,166
<i>how would you play it?</i>

130
00:06:51,125 --> 00:06:54,583
<i>I-I think I know.</i>

131
00:06:56,250 --> 00:07:01,416
♪♪

132
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:06,541
♪♪

133
00:07:06,625 --> 00:07:08,708
Ochiai:<i> The difference</i>
<i>is night and day.</i>

134
00:07:08,791 --> 00:07:11,666
Emi:<i> Suddenly the sound,</i>
<i>it's changing.</i>

135
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:18,625
♪♪

136
00:07:18,708 --> 00:07:19,083
<i>Kousei.</i>

137
00:07:19,166 --> 00:07:24,916
♪♪

138
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,166
[ Chuckles ]

139
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:26,458
Huh?

140
00:07:28,791 --> 00:07:30,000
<i>It's Saki.</i>

141
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,208
<i>I can hear her.</i>

142
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:34,416
[ Sighs ]

143
00:07:36,583 --> 00:07:37,500
Hiroko: Saki!

144
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:40,541
You have got to get
your act together!

145
00:07:40,625 --> 00:07:42,916
You just hit your son
until he bled!

146
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:43,875
You know that, right?

147
00:07:43,958 --> 00:07:46,291
What kind of a mom
does that?!

148
00:07:46,375 --> 00:07:48,125
What did he do?
What has he ever done,

149
00:07:48,208 --> 00:07:49,666
except try
and make you happy?!

150
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,416
Don't you think
I see that, Hiroko!

151
00:07:51,791 --> 00:07:52,791
Saki!

152
00:07:52,875 --> 00:07:58,958
♪♪

153
00:07:59,041 --> 00:08:00,666
He does his best.

154
00:08:01,083 --> 00:08:02,958
But...

155
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:04,791
[ Crying ]

156
00:08:04,875 --> 00:08:06,000
I'm out of time.

157
00:08:06,083 --> 00:08:09,000
This is all I can be.

158
00:08:10,875 --> 00:08:12,000
I know.

159
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:13,791
[ "Love's Sorrow" continues ]

160
00:08:13,875 --> 00:08:22,958
♪♪

161
00:08:23,041 --> 00:08:24,083
[ Kousei crying ]

162
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:26,666
Help me.

163
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:28,458
Please help me.

164
00:08:29,666 --> 00:08:31,791
Somebody help me.

165
00:08:31,875 --> 00:08:33,916
The notes on the piano...

166
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,958
where did they go?

167
00:08:37,041 --> 00:08:38,500
They're gone.

168
00:08:38,583 --> 00:08:40,000
I can't hear them.

169
00:08:40,083 --> 00:08:43,000
Somebody, somebody, help me.

170
00:08:43,083 --> 00:08:44,833
Mom.

171
00:08:44,916 --> 00:08:47,000
[ Sighs ]
<i>Kousei.</i>

172
00:08:47,083 --> 00:08:50,583
<i>I'm the one that tossed you</i>
<i>into the deep end.</i>

173
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:53,666
<i>She didn't want</i>
<i>to make you a pianist,</i>

174
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:55,041
<i>but I pushed her.</i>

175
00:08:57,083 --> 00:08:58,458
I'm sorry.

176
00:08:58,541 --> 00:09:00,166
<i>If all that Kousei</i>
<i>gets out of music</i>

177
00:09:00,250 --> 00:09:03,041
<i>are pain and suffering...</i>

178
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,791
Forgive me.

179
00:09:04,875 --> 00:09:06,041
<i>...then I should go.</i>

180
00:09:06,125 --> 00:09:08,833
<i>I've screwed up his life</i>
<i>enough already.</i>

181
00:09:08,916 --> 00:09:12,291
I didn't know.
I didn't know.

182
00:09:15,958 --> 00:09:16,958
Hiroko:<i> But now...</i>

183
00:09:19,625 --> 00:09:20,458
[ Crying ]

184
00:09:20,541 --> 00:09:23,125
<i>our Kousei is back.</i>

185
00:09:25,541 --> 00:09:28,041
<i>So what prompted</i>
<i>this unlikely miracle?</i>

186
00:09:28,125 --> 00:09:29,708
Kousei:<i> I just--</i>

187
00:09:29,791 --> 00:09:32,583
<i>I know I want to see it again,</i>
<i>no matter what.</i>

188
00:09:32,666 --> 00:09:34,541
<i>And since</i>
<i>that's the goal,</i>

189
00:09:34,625 --> 00:09:37,125
<i>maybe I should become</i>
<i>a crazy pianist, right?</i>

190
00:09:37,208 --> 00:09:38,541
[ Gasps ]

191
00:09:38,625 --> 00:09:39,833
Hiroko:
<i>Years after he lost his mother,</i>

192
00:09:39,916 --> 00:09:44,500
<i>he finds a girl</i>
<i>who means everything to him.</i>

193
00:09:44,583 --> 00:09:46,583
<i>It's not a lot to go off of,</i>

194
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:50,083
<i>but if it's enough to bring him</i>
<i>back to the land of the living,</i>

195
00:09:50,166 --> 00:09:52,541
<i>then, damn it, I believe.</i>

196
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:58,791
♪♪

197
00:09:58,875 --> 00:10:01,916
<i>Saki, you don't want</i>
<i>to miss this.</i>

198
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,791
<i>I know it's a little late,</i>

199
00:10:03,875 --> 00:10:06,958
<i>but he's finally ready</i>
<i>to say goodbye.</i>

200
00:10:07,041 --> 00:10:12,166
♪♪

201
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:14,000
Kousei:<i> Huh.</i>

202
00:10:14,083 --> 00:10:17,083
<i>This song brings back</i>
<i>memories of her.</i>

203
00:10:17,166 --> 00:10:21,750
<i>I even remember</i>
<i>how she used to smell.</i>

204
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:25,708
<i>When you play,</i>
<i>who's your song intended for?</i>

205
00:10:28,083 --> 00:10:29,125
<i>Will it reach her?</i>

206
00:10:29,208 --> 00:10:31,291
<i>I hope it does.</i>

207
00:10:31,375 --> 00:10:32,958
Saki:
What's he going to do...

208
00:10:33,041 --> 00:10:35,666
after I'm gone?

209
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:38,208
Can he make a life
of this?

210
00:10:38,291 --> 00:10:41,250
[ Sobs ] Tell me I've taught
him
that much, at least.

211
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:43,791
There was no time
for the art of it.

212
00:10:43,875 --> 00:10:48,500
All I could do was force him
to play exactly what's
written.

213
00:10:48,583 --> 00:10:51,708
So long as
he can do that,

214
00:10:51,791 --> 00:10:54,750
maybe the piano
will support him someday.

215
00:10:55,875 --> 00:10:57,458
What a terrible mother...

216
00:10:57,541 --> 00:11:01,166
leaving her baby
all alone like this.

217
00:11:02,875 --> 00:11:07,833
I wonder, will he remember
to brush his teeth?

218
00:11:07,916 --> 00:11:09,958
He falls asleep
anywhere.

219
00:11:10,041 --> 00:11:11,833
What if
he catches a cold?

220
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:16,125
He'll want
to play sports later.

221
00:11:16,208 --> 00:11:18,291
What if
he hurts himself?

222
00:11:19,625 --> 00:11:21,291
I wish that...

223
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:24,250
we could have had
more time together.

224
00:11:25,375 --> 00:11:28,166
Kousei,
my little treasure,

225
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:30,458
will you ever
find happiness?

226
00:11:30,541 --> 00:11:36,208
♪♪

227
00:11:36,291 --> 00:11:39,041
<i>I should have known.</i>

228
00:11:39,125 --> 00:11:41,708
<i>The ghost of my mother</i>
<i>was a shadow I created...</i>

229
00:11:43,666 --> 00:11:45,041
<i>my weakness personified</i>

230
00:11:45,125 --> 00:11:47,250
<i>and my guilt.</i>

231
00:11:48,916 --> 00:11:52,791
<i>Mom isn't out there</i>
<i>judging me from afar.</i>

232
00:11:53,375 --> 00:11:54,708
<i>She's here.</i>

233
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:59,500
<i>She's a part of me.</i>

234
00:11:59,583 --> 00:12:01,875
<i>Yes, of course.</i>

235
00:12:01,958 --> 00:12:03,833
<i>The piano...</i>

236
00:12:03,916 --> 00:12:05,000
<i>you don't play it.</i>

237
00:12:05,083 --> 00:12:06,041
<i>You embrace it.</i>

238
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:14,750
♪♪

239
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:17,041
Young Kousei: Hey, Mom,
tell me something.

240
00:12:17,125 --> 00:12:19,541
If there's a song
called "Love's Joy"

241
00:12:19,625 --> 00:12:20,708
and one called
"Love's Sorrow,"

242
00:12:20,791 --> 00:12:24,208
how come you always
just play the second one?

243
00:12:24,291 --> 00:12:26,833
[ Gasps ]

244
00:12:26,916 --> 00:12:29,125
I play it...

245
00:12:29,208 --> 00:12:30,458
[ Chuckles ]

246
00:12:31,833 --> 00:12:35,458
...so that sorrow
won't be as scary.

247
00:12:37,250 --> 00:12:39,125
Hiroko:<i> Nobody's alone</i>
<i>in this life.</i>

248
00:12:39,208 --> 00:12:42,250
<i>We're all notes</i>
<i>in one big coloratura,</i>

249
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:44,500
<i>wholes, halves, quarter notes.</i>

250
00:12:44,583 --> 00:12:47,958
<i>Music connects us</i>
<i>with the people we know</i>

251
00:12:48,041 --> 00:12:49,541
<i>and with the people we don't...</i>

252
00:12:50,416 --> 00:12:52,083
<i>all the people in the world.</i>

253
00:12:52,166 --> 00:12:56,583
♪♪

254
00:12:56,666 --> 00:12:58,458
Kaori:<i> You should come along.</i>

255
00:13:01,291 --> 00:13:02,458
Kousei:<i> I'm connected to Kaori,</i>

256
00:13:02,541 --> 00:13:05,458
<i>and I'm connected to Mom.</i>

257
00:13:05,541 --> 00:13:07,250
<i>Now that I know that much,</i>

258
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:07,708
<i>I can move forward.</i>

259
00:13:09,208 --> 00:13:11,083
<i>So...</i>

260
00:13:11,166 --> 00:13:12,083
<i>so...</i>

261
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:18,125
♪♪

262
00:13:18,208 --> 00:13:19,333
<i>goodbye.</i>

263
00:13:19,416 --> 00:13:21,958
[ Music ends ]

264
00:13:30,208 --> 00:13:32,333
[ Bench scrapes ]

265
00:13:32,416 --> 00:13:34,541
[ Footsteps echoing ]

266
00:13:40,375 --> 00:13:43,166
[ Applause ]

267
00:13:56,291 --> 00:13:56,750
[ Sighs ]

268
00:13:59,583 --> 00:14:02,375
[ Footsteps echoing ]

269
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:08,166
<i>Goodbye.</i>

270
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:10,750
[ Gasps ]

271
00:14:15,166 --> 00:14:17,000
[ Footsteps echoing ]

272
00:14:22,458 --> 00:14:23,916
[ Thump ]
[ Gasps ]

273
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,000
[ Shudders ]

274
00:14:26,083 --> 00:14:28,125
I got weak in the knees.

275
00:14:28,208 --> 00:14:30,041
Guess that took a lot out of me.

276
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:32,041
Huh?
Hiroko: Kousei!

277
00:14:32,125 --> 00:14:34,375
Kousei!

278
00:14:34,458 --> 00:14:35,500
[ Grunts ]

279
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:37,125
[ Wails ]

280
00:14:37,208 --> 00:14:39,250
[ Crying ]

281
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:40,541
[ Hiroko chuckles ]

282
00:14:40,625 --> 00:14:42,541
Can't call you
Mr. Quitter today.

283
00:14:42,625 --> 00:14:44,708
She's throwing herself
at boys already?

284
00:14:44,791 --> 00:14:47,291
I see gray hair
in my future.

285
00:14:47,958 --> 00:14:50,125
[ Koharu murmuring ]

286
00:14:50,208 --> 00:14:51,708
[ Gasps ]

287
00:14:52,583 --> 00:14:54,375
Your mom, you saw her?

288
00:14:54,458 --> 00:14:57,166
[ Gasps ]

289
00:14:57,250 --> 00:14:58,375
She's with me...

290
00:14:58,458 --> 00:15:00,375
always.

291
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:02,458
I know that now.

292
00:15:02,541 --> 00:15:03,875
Yeah.

293
00:15:03,958 --> 00:15:07,125
I reach for the keys
the same way she did.

294
00:15:07,208 --> 00:15:09,541
I press the pedals
the same way.

295
00:15:09,625 --> 00:15:12,875
The things that I like,
even how I eat...

296
00:15:14,125 --> 00:15:15,291
It's like she lives on

297
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:17,041
in every little thing
that I do.

298
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:23,416
My mom and I,
we're connected.

299
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:25,458
[ Sighs ]

300
00:15:27,666 --> 00:15:32,416
Hiroko, do you think
it reached her?

301
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:34,750
[ Crying ]

302
00:15:34,833 --> 00:15:38,083
I played the song
as well as I could.

303
00:15:38,166 --> 00:15:40,291
Do you think
that my mom could hear it?

304
00:15:40,375 --> 00:15:43,125
[ Crying ]

305
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:48,291
Dummy. You just told me
you're connected, right?

306
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:51,291
You can bet your ass
she did.

307
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:56,375
[ Sobbing ]

308
00:15:56,458 --> 00:16:02,875
♪♪

309
00:16:02,958 --> 00:16:08,416
♪♪

310
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:10,083
Kousei:<i> Thanks to music,</i>

311
00:16:10,166 --> 00:16:12,625
<i>I've met people</i>
<i>I never would have known.</i>

312
00:16:12,708 --> 00:16:16,500
<i>And every person that I've met,</i>

313
00:16:16,583 --> 00:16:18,541
<i>they've changed me somehow.</i>

314
00:16:19,375 --> 00:16:21,333
<i>What brought me back to life...</i>

315
00:16:22,041 --> 00:16:24,375
<i>you gave me this.</i>

316
00:16:24,458 --> 00:16:27,708
<i>a heart full of memories</i>
<i>I only possess</i>

317
00:16:27,791 --> 00:16:30,458
<i>because you taught me</i>
<i>to play the piano.</i>

318
00:16:31,541 --> 00:16:33,250
<i>I'm happy, Mom.</i>

319
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:34,458
<i>I really am.</i>

320
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,250
<i>Thank you.</i>

321
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:39,541
<i>Thank you.</i>

322
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:45,000
<i>Goodbye.</i>

323
00:16:45,083 --> 00:16:47,666
-Wow, that was exquisite.
-Wow.

324
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:49,500
Man: Really, I could
just go home now.

325
00:16:49,583 --> 00:16:51,375
[ Applause ]

326
00:16:51,458 --> 00:16:53,083
Man #2: Oh, right.
There's one left.

327
00:16:53,166 --> 00:16:55,083
I don't think
I'm ready for more.

328
00:16:57,083 --> 00:17:00,208
Miike:<i> I've never been so scared</i>
<i>to go out onstage before.</i>

329
00:17:00,291 --> 00:17:01,875
<i>Unfortunate.</i>

330
00:17:01,958 --> 00:17:03,958
<i>That's a tough act</i>
<i>to follow.</i>

331
00:17:04,041 --> 00:17:06,208
<i>I want to run away.</i>

332
00:17:06,291 --> 00:17:07,416
[ Gasps ]

333
00:17:10,375 --> 00:17:11,500
<i>Mom.</i>

334
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:17,458
<i>Could I have played</i>
<i>my heart out like he did?</i>

335
00:17:17,541 --> 00:17:18,833
<i>Could I have played</i>

336
00:17:18,916 --> 00:17:20,583
<i>with as much sincerity?</i>

337
00:17:22,083 --> 00:17:23,500
<i>Maybe--</i>

338
00:17:23,583 --> 00:17:26,541
<i>Maybe I can give it my all</i>
<i>like Arima.</i>

339
00:17:27,291 --> 00:17:28,166
<i>One way to find out.</i>

340
00:17:30,041 --> 00:17:31,333
<i>Watch me.</i>

341
00:17:33,125 --> 00:17:35,041
[ Playing "Violin Sonata
in E minor, Opus 82" ]

342
00:17:35,125 --> 00:17:37,708
<i>Right now, all I want</i>
<i>is to hear my Mom's voice.</i>

343
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:41,125
-[ Gasping ]
<i>-What?</i>

344
00:17:41,208 --> 00:17:44,541
<i>That's a bit pianissimo</i>
<i>for Miike.</i>

345
00:17:44,625 --> 00:17:48,250
<i>I see. You weren't</i>
<i>immune to it, either.</i>

346
00:17:49,458 --> 00:17:51,166
<i>Arima's piece,</i>

347
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:52,833
<i>it's raising the bar.</i>

348
00:17:52,916 --> 00:17:55,375
♪♪

349
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:58,875
[ Crowd murmuring ]

350
00:17:58,958 --> 00:18:01,041
Ah,
that was amazing!

351
00:18:01,125 --> 00:18:02,541
All in all,
a fine concert.

352
00:18:02,625 --> 00:18:05,250
You know...
Hmm?

353
00:18:05,333 --> 00:18:08,416
I think being a musician's
the best.

354
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:11,333
[ Chuckles ]

355
00:18:11,416 --> 00:18:13,208
Conquering an evil foe,

356
00:18:13,291 --> 00:18:15,458
there's nothing like it
in the whole world.

357
00:18:15,541 --> 00:18:17,000
<i>That's what she likes</i>
<i>about it?</i>

358
00:18:17,083 --> 00:18:18,500
There he is,
dead ahead,

359
00:18:18,583 --> 00:18:19,666
the man of the hour!

360
00:18:19,750 --> 00:18:21,583
Hey! [ Laughs ]

361
00:18:21,666 --> 00:18:24,375
Kousei, you --

362
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:28,333
[ Heart beats ]

363
00:18:28,416 --> 00:18:30,375
<i>Huh?</i>

364
00:18:30,458 --> 00:18:33,250
<i>What the...</i>

365
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:35,208
<i>This is so weird.</i>

366
00:18:35,291 --> 00:18:38,583
<i>It's like I don't</i>
<i>know what to say.</i>

367
00:18:38,666 --> 00:18:39,041
<i>Freaky.</i>

368
00:18:41,625 --> 00:18:42,500
You sure
you don't got to stick around?

369
00:18:42,583 --> 00:18:44,875
Nah, it's fine.

370
00:18:44,958 --> 00:18:47,125
I came out here to play,
and that's what I did.

371
00:18:47,208 --> 00:18:48,708
And now...

372
00:18:48,791 --> 00:18:50,250
time to track down
little Miss No-show

373
00:18:50,333 --> 00:18:52,416
and find out
why she bailed on me!

374
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:52,958
He's really mad.

375
00:18:53,041 --> 00:18:54,458
Yeah. You think?

376
00:18:54,541 --> 00:18:56,125
Let's call it a day.

377
00:18:56,208 --> 00:18:57,625
I'm wiped out,
you guys.

378
00:18:57,708 --> 00:18:59,166
I want a juice box.

379
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:01,666
Hmm. Cut me in for some,
and you got yourself a deal.

380
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:03,958
[ Laughs ]
Kousei: Tsubaki.

381
00:19:04,041 --> 00:19:05,666
Hey, you're being
awfully quiet there.

382
00:19:05,750 --> 00:19:06,708
So what did you think?

383
00:19:06,791 --> 00:19:09,625
Well, I think...

384
00:19:09,708 --> 00:19:11,291
you look pretty grown-up.

385
00:19:11,375 --> 00:19:12,416
[ Laughs ]

386
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:13,333
I mean my playing.

387
00:19:13,416 --> 00:19:14,541
Would a compliment
kill you?

388
00:19:14,625 --> 00:19:16,875
[ Gasps ]

389
00:19:16,958 --> 00:19:17,500
<i>What?</i>

390
00:19:17,583 --> 00:19:19,833
<i>What the heck?</i>

391
00:19:19,916 --> 00:19:21,916
<i>You weirdo.</i>

392
00:19:22,958 --> 00:19:23,791
<i>How come I feel like...</i>

393
00:19:23,875 --> 00:19:26,583
<i>I'm gonna start crying?</i>

394
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:27,750
<i>What for?</i>

395
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:30,416
<i>Are they tears of relief</i>

396
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,750
<i>'cause we talk</i>
<i>like nothing was different?</i>

397
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:35,916
<i>Or tears of regret</i>
<i>because...</i>

398
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,458
[ Drops echoing ]
<i>...I really hoped it would be?</i>

399
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:42,708
[ Insects buzzing ]

400
00:19:44,833 --> 00:19:47,500
[ Playing "Nocturne in D-flat
Major, Opus 27, Number 2" ]

401
00:19:47,583 --> 00:19:54,833
♪♪

402
00:19:54,916 --> 00:19:56,500
It wouldn't have
killed you to come up

403
00:19:56,583 --> 00:19:58,583
and say hello to me
at the concert, you know.

404
00:19:58,666 --> 00:19:59,708
That said, you keeping
your distance at the show

405
00:19:59,791 --> 00:20:02,750
was classic Ochiai.

406
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,375
[ Sighs ] I admit
I was surprised

407
00:20:04,458 --> 00:20:07,000
to hear you're mentoring
the boy, and with good reason.

408
00:20:07,083 --> 00:20:10,458
After all, you made yourself
right scarce

409
00:20:10,541 --> 00:20:11,541
after poor Saki
passed away.

410
00:20:11,625 --> 00:20:13,833
[ Sighs ]

411
00:20:13,916 --> 00:20:16,291
You're not the only one
who's changed.

412
00:20:16,375 --> 00:20:18,333
It's clear
he's evolving as a pianist.

413
00:20:18,416 --> 00:20:20,541
Yeah.

414
00:20:21,791 --> 00:20:23,333
He's taking
what's inside him

415
00:20:23,416 --> 00:20:26,416
and playing it
for all to hear.

416
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:27,833
I think...

417
00:20:27,916 --> 00:20:32,541
he's finally moving forward
as an honest-to-God artist.

418
00:20:32,625 --> 00:20:34,500
[ Insects buzzing ]

419
00:20:34,583 --> 00:20:35,708
[ Hiroko sighs ]

420
00:20:35,791 --> 00:20:38,708
Look, losing Saki
was a tragedy.

421
00:20:38,791 --> 00:20:40,750
It damn near
shattered me,

422
00:20:40,833 --> 00:20:43,083
and I know for a fact
it shattered him.

423
00:20:43,166 --> 00:20:45,666
Sure, it forced him
to grow as a musician.

424
00:20:45,750 --> 00:20:49,041
Fair enough, but that's one hell
of a price to pay.

425
00:20:49,125 --> 00:20:51,500
[ Sighs ]

426
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:53,291
Ochiai:
<i>Everything Arima plays now</i>

427
00:20:53,375 --> 00:20:55,583
<i>is tinged with a quiet sorrow.</i>

428
00:20:55,666 --> 00:20:58,875
<i>If his growth as of late</i>
<i>was set into motion</i>

429
00:20:58,958 --> 00:21:01,458
<i>by his mother's death, then...</i>

430
00:21:01,541 --> 00:21:04,916
<i>I fear he's on a painful path.</i>

431
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,541
[ Insects buzzing ]

432
00:21:08,083 --> 00:21:10,541
<i>And if he means</i>
<i>to tread this path...</i>

433
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,041
<i>the day might</i>
<i>eventually come...</i>

434
00:21:16,125 --> 00:21:17,583
[ Buzzing fades ]

435
00:21:17,666 --> 00:21:20,083
<i>...when the muses</i>
<i>demand another loss.</i>

436
00:21:21,458 --> 00:21:23,583
[ "Orange" playing ]
[ Singing in Japanese ]

437
00:21:23,666 --> 00:21:34,000
♪♪

438
00:21:34,083 --> 00:21:42,666
♪♪

439
00:21:42,750 --> 00:21:53,125
♪♪

440
00:21:53,208 --> 00:22:02,583
♪♪

441
00:22:02,666 --> 00:22:12,208
♪♪

442
00:22:12,291 --> 00:22:21,666
♪♪

443
00:22:21,750 --> 00:22:31,333
♪♪

444
00:22:31,416 --> 00:22:40,708
♪♪

445
